WEBVTT

00:03:29.471 --> 00:03:33.368
"Kamau, the students
who spend most of the time in the Fab Lab

00:03:33.392 --> 00:03:34.780
are failing their exams."

00:03:35.251 --> 00:03:36.828
I said, "What do you mean?"

00:03:37.791 --> 00:03:40.179
And I looked into it, and he was right,

00:03:40.203 --> 00:03:41.766
and the reason they were failing

00:03:41.790 --> 00:03:44.581
is that they'd honed their skills
so well in certain things

00:03:44.605 --> 00:03:48.057
that they were going out into the city
and offering services for money.

00:03:48.081 --> 00:03:49.498
So they were making money --

00:03:49.522 --> 00:03:50.573
(Laughter)

00:03:50.597 --> 00:03:53.328
and they therefore
weren't focusing on their studies.

00:03:53.352 --> 00:03:55.409
And I thought,
what a good problem to have.

00:03:55.433 --> 00:03:56.449
(Laughter)

00:03:56.473 --> 00:03:58.584
Don't quote me on that.
I'm an academician.

00:03:59.613 --> 00:04:02.217
So we needed to scale this,